Version 1.4 - Updated store images to give a better overview of this font. Also updated the alt key document and script to display all 174 usable font characters.
Version 1.5 - a) Added this Version History Document to coincide with the rest of my assets
b) Removed unused Resources Folder from project
c) Added Documentation Folder and moved Alt Key Document and Version History

Version 1.6 Fixes - Major update to Font TTF file, removed all unwanted                      pixels that were effecting several letters, for example                    the heart character had a pixel at the left bottom, not                    suppose to be there.

Version 1.6 - Please re-download if you have downloaded previously this before 22/02/2015 and reinstall it to your operating system, if you had already installed it to the OS. else just replace the TTF file by downloading again from the asset store and overwrite the old TTF file.
Version 1.7 - Upgrade demo scene & script to use new UI system instead of the old GUI.
Version 1.8 - upgrade this package to Unity 5
Version 2.0 - a) changed font demo scene to match other store fonts  (e.g text colour, added UI sprite)
b) change store icons to match other store fonts
m_Text: You can also see here the number of days till election day.
m_Text: You can hover over an action to see what resources you'll gain or lose
m_Text: The current vote distribution can be seen here. The number on the left
is the number of votes you have.
m_Text: These actions give you resources and votes, though some come at the cost
m_Text: You'll also have to manage resources like Influence and money.
m_Text: The main bulk of the game would be managing how you spend your time using
m_Text: 'Welcome to Majority Ruling! Your goal is to secure the majority of the
hit Esc to open the Options menu)'
m_Text: Each timeslot can be spent doing one of the actions in this list.
m_Text: Once all the timeslots have an action, click Execute to perform them and
m_Text: 'Beware that your opponent will also get a set number of votes at the end
of each day, so try to stay on top!
m_Text: When your stress hits 100, you'll faint and lose two days of the campaign,
m_Text: To help you out, you can Talk to the Masses once a day to get one neutral
or disliked message from a certain group.
m_Text: That's all you need to know. Good luck in your campaign!
m_Text: Congratulations on making it to Level 2! This level introduces some new
m_Text: 'Voting also works differently. Voters are split into multiple groups,
and each group has 1 unique liked and disliked message. '
m_Text: When selecting the "Speech" action, you have to choose a topic to address
and a group to say it to.
m_Text: Firstly, you'll now have to manage your stress, which goes up by 5 with
every action except for actions that let you relax.
m_Text: You'll gain 10 votes if the group likes your message, 5 votes if they're
neutral, but you'll lose 5 points if they dislike it.
m_Text: Created by Chan Ger Hean, Steven Chua,  Loo Xin Wei, and Kenneth Hong.

description: It's time to take a break man. Look at you! You look like you're going
- It was a rainy day and you were feeling tired while attending classes.
- Oh no you were caught and your influence was reduced!
- It was hard, but you were able to keep awake throughout the lesson.
- You found some change lying on the floor. Today must be your lucky day!
- It was a normal sunny day. Nothing in particular happened.
- As you pass through the corridor, you hear whispers behind you.
- '"I heard they never brush their teeth...I bet their breath smells like rotten
- '"Yeah, no way I''d want a dogbreath for president."'
- '"Hey, my wallet''s in your bag!" your classmate points to your open backpack.'
- You swear that you didn't steal it and someone must've planted it there, but
- '"Hey, did you study for the test today?" your classmate asks.'
- '"Wait, there was a test today??? Oh sh-"'
- The fire alarm sounds! Fortunately, you were able to skip the Chinese test next
- You're minding your own business when a classmate walks up to you.
- '"Hey, um, I know we don''t know each other much, but do you wanna go out for
- All the other students in the classroom secretly go "aww".
- The School Newspaper covers your campaign and gives you more recognition.
- '"Bold Student Spends All Their Time Campaigning Instead of Having A Life"'
- As you pass through the corridor, you hear whispers behind you.
- '"Ugh, did you know that they don''t like dogs? Like, excuse me??"'
- '"What a sick human being. I bet they secretly eat them for lunch, too!"'
- A low humming sound spread throughout the district.
- When you wake up, reports surface which describes beams of light from the sky
- Your opponent gained 2 Votes in District {0}.
- Logging onto social media, you see a trending post with your name on it...
- A fake photo has surfaced of you playing an M-rated dating simulator!
- You hear a soft meow coming from a dark alley...
- A cute cat emerges from the alley and starts purring and rubbing against your
- You decide to adopt it and news of this spreads like wildfire!
- '*Cough Cough* You begin to feel a little feverish...'
- 'You struggle to find your thermometer and measure your temperature: 38.2 degrees!'
- With the election day drawing closer and closer, you feel the pressure slowly
- Oh! A new letter came in the mail!
- It's a notification from the Lottery Committee!
- You won a small prize in the Lottery!
- I guess I've been thinking too much then
- Phew! What a tiring day campaigning to the public! Time to head home...
- You spot something on a windshield...
- Breaking News! Riots have broken out all over the Country!
- Some say its due to stress levels reaching an all time high...
- Others say it was over a pot of curry...
- Oh! A new letter came in the mail!
- A bright postcard with floral designs on it came out of the envelope!
- 'It reads: "Please enjoy this free spa coupon on us! Good Luck in your campaign!"'
- Maybe campaigning for president really has its perks!
- Word spreads on how you were an amazing School President!
- All those days you spent on student politics weren't a complete waste of time!
- "Boy: Hey you, you\u2019re finally awake. You were trying to cross the border
right? Walked right into that Imperial ambush same as us and that thief over
- Isn't this... the front of my school? What... was I doing here....
- Even though I am running for president, I am still doing part time jobs huh?
- Time to win the elections to become a full time president!
- Do you want to proceed to the next level or return to main menu?
- You've been covered by the school magazine!
